Hi,

resolving an issue as "Duplicate" should require a Ticket-ID as reference and it should either link it together and/or add a comment that this issue has been resolved as a duplicate of ...
Example:
{code}
*** This Issue has been marked as a duplicate of Issue TICKETREFERENCE ***
{code}

Also, the referenced issue should get a comment like:
{code}
*** Issue DUPLICATEDTICKETID has been marked as a duplicate of this issue. ***
{code}


Otherwise it's a pain to figure out what the actual duplicate is/was because people tend to just close it as "Duplicate" with no more information unless you make it mandatory.

